Cloud adoption requires selecting appropriate service models depending on workload needs.

IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
IaaS provides full control over compute, storage, and networking.
- Suitable for hosting SAP application servers
- Enables customization and scalability
- Example: Amazon EC2, VPC

PaaS (Platform as a Service)
PaaS offers managed services that reduce administrative overhead.
- Supports database modernization and automation
- Improves deployment efficiency
- Example: Amazon RDS, AWS Lambda

SaaS (Software as a Service)
SaaS delivers fully managed cloud services.
- Useful for monitoring, backup, and enterprise tools
- Minimizes infrastructure responsibility
- Example: Amazon S3, CloudWatch

This evaluation supports selecting an optimal hybrid deployment approach for SAP workloads.
